               The mass of an object remains constant regardless of location, so the sand bag's mass is still 5 kg. Weight depends on gravity: on Earth, with a weight of 50 N and mass of 5 kg, the gravitational acceleration is 10 m/s². On a planet with half the gravity, the gravitational acceleration is 5 m/s², so the weight becomes 5 kg × 5 m/s² = 25 N.

