**B. Protein synthesis** – Antibiotics like tetracyclines, macrolides, and aminoglycosides target bacterial ribosomes. ✅ Affected.

**C. DNA synthesis** – Antibiotics like fluoroquinolones inhibit bacterial DNA gyrase or topoisomerase, affecting DNA synthesis. ✅ Affected.

**D. Reverse transcriptase** – This enzyme is used by retroviruses (like HIV) to convert RNA into DNA. Bacteria do not have reverse transcriptase as part of their normal life cycle, so antibiotics targeting bacteria do not inhibit reverse transcriptase. ❌ Not affected.

